        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "[Common].[usp_NewBillingPeriodProcesses]",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update the status of accounts at the beginning of a new billing period. Specifically, it changes the status of accounts from '46' to 'AC' and logs the current billing period and the user who authenticated the change. This procedure is part of the processes that need to be executed at the start of a new billing cycle."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a single update operation on the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.Account",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. It does not involve complex logic, multiple steps, or intricate data manipulations."
        }
      ]
    },
